commit.message: Added Tom's changes (csv functionality, needs testing)
Add texlive-latex-extra to image for a4wide
changed the wd to work on docker
Now downloads all of the surveys and rds file as a zip. Now downloads the csv results file. Two buttons were added for them
Hopefully fixed the bug this time. Think it had to do with global variables not being reset if page was refreshed.

Hopefully fixed bug with survey creation on hosted server involving directory issues. Added the ability to upload a zip file of filled out pds and rds file that will be used to generate the csv file of examined survey data. Added helpful in progress messages during survey generation and zip file upload.
Modularize dockerfile r installation, update install
Added constraints to how many total questions, short answer questions, and answers can be added. Helpful error messages will alert the user during the survey creation.
Updated Dockerfile to include texlive for doc converting
Updated image for authentication and startup
Added header options to mitigate security risks in accordance with a simple penetration test performed with OWASP's zaproxy
